linkedLists

Interface ListInterface<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of object to be stored in the list.
    All Superinterfaces:
    abstractDataTypes.AbstractDataInterface<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractList, DoubleLinkedList, LinkedList

    public interface ListInterface<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>, abstractDataTypes.AbstractDataInterface<T>
    This interface declares the methods for a linked list class.
    Author:
    kevna (Aaron Moore)

      • add

        void add(ListInterface<T> list)
        Adds the contents of another list to this list, not specifying the position. Ideally this will make recursive calls of add(Object) by iterating through the contents of 'list'.
        Parameters:
        list - List of items to add to this list.
